(439, 'BRC on Anu Engineer (main CoFo) from [Ajay Agarwal](https://www.linkedin.com/in/ajay-agrawal-aa79b12/?originalSubdomain=in) (Sirion Labs) done by @Aakash 2025-05-25: On email to @Rajat Agarwal 1. happy to speak and share me experiences w/ Anu. 1. BTW, I’m investing 500k in the SAFE round as well. Anu''s Key Strengths - Technical excellence and clear communication - Strong ability to simplify complex problems into simple language - Skilled at breaking down complex problems for both executives and production teams - Distributed team management capabilities - Successfully led 100% distributed edge team pre-COVID - Managed team of 24 (6 in Seattle, 18 globally) at Sirion - Strong at maintaining tight cadence with distributed teams - Personal qualities - Very humble and grounded approach - Direct but not confrontational in disagreements - Highly transparent in communications - Strong customer empathy and friendly demeanor Technical Leadership Experience - At Sirion: - Managed parallel engineering team of 20-25 people - Focused on AI-native stack for auto-extraction - Led implementation of BERT/Roberta models - Currently 1,200 different models deployed at Sirion - Strong technical followership - Demonstrated ability to quickly build technical teams - Successfully recruited past team members across multiple companies - Highly adaptable to new technologies - Stays current with latest developments - Research-oriented mindset - Quick to implement new approaches Areas for Support/Watch-o...'),
(443, 'Analysis by dev - 2026-02-04: ### Company Snapshot Problem & solution Soulside Al offers an Integrated AI platform for High-Acuity Behavioral Healthcare to automate compliance and documentation, addressing workforce strain (clinician turnover, documentation time) and rising claim denials/regulatory pressure. Key product claims include automated documentation and audit workflows, a FineTuning Engine for rapid payer requirement updates, and a voiceprint-based Group AI. Outcomes cited: reduce documentation time by ~80%, lower claim denials by up to 25%, faster claim submission (4 days vs 22), and avoidance of clawbacks. Ideal customer profile and pricing Target market: Moderate‑high acuity Behavioral Health (including mental health, substance use, eating disorders), with multi-location facilities. Immediate market sizing highlights in the deck point to ~35K facilities as the addressable base. Pricing signals include: ACV pricing ranges around $85–$250 per license per month; additional pricing cues show per-intervention pricing and multi‑product potential (documentation and compliance). Immediate SAM ~ $27B; SOM in the 10–15% range within the near term (3–4B) per the provided sizing slides; TAM cited as $240B with a longer‑term SAM ~ $150B. Status of product & traction highlight Live revenue as of Jan 2026 with ongoing pilots; notable milestones include: - Feb 2025: first revenue; Jul 2025: second customer; Oct–Nov 2025: one customer per week; Dec 2025: >$500K ARR; Jan 2026: live...'),
(444, 'Conversation notes with @Rahul Mathur from 09.07.2024: 1. Founders: 1. [Apurwa Masook](https://www.linkedin.com/in/apurwamasook/?originalSubdomain=in) — ISRO (internship) 1. [Sudarshan Samal](https://www.linkedin.com/in/sudarshan-samal-0267686b/?originalSubdomain=in) – L&T & ISRO (internship) 1. About Co-Fos 1. All from Orissa 1. Went to the same college - VSS Univ of Tech in Burla 1. 2nd year of college is when they began building rockets (2016) 1. None have aerospace background / family background in Govt services 1. Apurwa had a brief internship stint with ISRO in 2018 1. Discovery of rockets happened during alumni day event 1. College had got a ₹50L Grant from ISRO → hence had facilities 1. Worked on a project for local dam → to figure out where sedimentation & silting was taking place 1. Business 1. Order book (includes 2 POs and 1x iDEX order) ~ ₹35 crore at MOQ 1. Since they are building solid propellant→ this comes under export control 1. So while market is global; it requires G2G tie-ups to enable EXIM 1. Will need to invest ₹20 crore into CAPEX for facility 1. Facility needs to be on land which they BUY or LEASE for 99 years since license to do explosives is tied to the location of use 1. Will explore getting land from a defense corridor 1. Fundraising 1. Raised ~7 months ago ₹52 crore pre-money → ₹7 crore raise 1. From Angels only 1. HVB Angels invested $300K 1. Current round will be ₹30 crore on ~ ₹120 crore pre-money 1. In IC with Mounttech (Former Def Secretary’...'),
